notesStmt.note: Ownership inscription and date 1723 (p. i); a large number of early recipes are in the hand of Kendrick. A number of recipes are added in several later hands, some 19th century, undated.
List of contents [compiled by bookseller?] is shelved with the manuscript.

msContents.summary: Comprises numerous recipes for wines -- damson, birch, balm, raisin, gooseberry, elder, cowerslap [cowslip], lemon, currant, and mead, among others. Includes recipes for tansies, puddings, cheesecakes, cakes, soups, fish, oysters, preserving meats, pickles, and preserves, with a few household recipes and medicinal recipes for green ointment and a cure for jaundice.

supportDesc.foliation: 182 leaves; [iv], 1-360 modern pagination in pencil, upper center.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in various cursive scripts by several hands.

origin.p: Written in England, from 1723 (p. i) to the 19th century[?].
